<br>
Sol Ro faction is rediculously easy to fix, just AE shadowed men, or hand some dervish rings to Ortallis, or give 30gp to Rathmana, etc.  There's no reason to put a faction reset in game for this faction.<br>
<br>
There is an NPC who helps with truespirit faction in ToSR.  Unfortunately, I can't recall the name.  He's new, as of say 9 months or so, and not in Ilia's Bestiary just yet.  To find the little bugger, you've got to do some exploring.  He's in one of the bedrooms of the Temple, you have to open a bunch of doors and wander around to find him.  I think you're confusing the hailing part with the warning about not hailing Tazgar the Efreeti and lowering your Sol Ro faction.  You don't hail this guy, just pop him, IIRC.  Find the one guy here who doesn't con the same as everyone else, preferably not named 'a plasmatic priest' so you don't get owned by a cleric epic NPC.  <br>
<br>
And yes, the shammy epic beginning will help if you don't wanna go through this route or want higher faction JIC something else with this quest is fubarred.  Resetting your TS faction drops you right back to the point in the epic we all start at, low apprehensive, which means you have to redo the first steps all over again.  Up to you really, 2k and another game of find the missing NPCs, or haul the same crappy jewel from BB/FoB/OOT to NFP ad nauseum.<br>
